>trying to prove the definition of the cross product and why it came 
>about I started by defining a vector c perpendicular to two vectors 
>a and b. then I produced two dot product equations ie a1*c1 + a2*c2 
>+ a3*c3 = 0 as well as b1*c1 + b2c2 + b3c3 = 0. I then find the 
>components of the vector c in terms of the components of a and b and 
>eventually get a system of components with c3 = c3 I am stuck from 
>here!
